@@ -0,0 +1,5 @@
+# Solution
+
+`get()` returned cached values without moving their keys to the most-recently-used end of the `OrderedDict`, so a recently read entry could still be evicted as the oldest entry. It now refreshes the key's recency after confirming that the entry has not expired.
+
+`put()` evicted an entry whenever the cache was full, even when the key being written already existed and therefore required no additional capacity. Eviction is now limited to insertion of a new key into a full cache, while updates replace the value and mark the key as most recently used.
